  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rapid Ebola Awareness, Communication and Training Program (REACT)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Implementing with Africare, PCI is implementing a six month Ebola prevention program through the extension of PCI&apos;s USAID funded LAUNCH program. REACT will work to to prevent the spread of Ebola in Bong and Nimba Counties and support key health institutions in Bong and Nimba to provide safe patient care. PCI will work to mobilize these communities and support them by building the capacity of health care providers in patient care and infection control; reinforce contact tracing and surveillance to stop transmission of disease; and provide Personal Protective Equipment (PPEs) and other needed supplies to health centers. REACT will target 795,507 beneficiaries with the restoration of health services paired with community health education and behavior change, and clinical support. Another 1,810 beneficiaries will be reached with the provision of critical non-food items related to clinical support. A targeted 2,800 Community Health Workers will be trained and supported, including 1200 Traditional Trained Midwives and 1,600 General Community Health Volunteers, with a total 636,406 community members utilizing targeted health education message practices. React will also support/rehabilitate 6 health centers, 96 health clinics and 1 health post.

To effectively address the outbreak PCI will be focusing on three components: 
(i) Proper testing, isolation, and care of infected individuals, and infection control in treatment 

centers; 
(ii) Large-scale behavior change strategies that reduce communities&#x2019; exposure to the virus and 
break the chain of transmission. 
(iii) Effective tracing of individuals suspected of having come in contact with affected persons and 
monitoring them for symptoms.</narrative>
  </description>
